widgets_values: the front-facing staff member is holding the object close to camera, label fully visible in center area. From here onward refer to it only as 'the object.' Other characters remain front/3/4-facing, watching with concerned expressions. Lighting changes to a soft key highlight on the object to emphasize form; a gentle rack focus moves from faces to the object. Micro-movements: the staff member makes only small wrist tilts to show the nozzle and handle (no full rotation), a customer points with an outstretched front-facing hand (not covering the object). Camera performs a subtle 1.05x zoom in and slight, smooth depth shift ‚Äî keep the object centered and visible throughout. End state: the staff member lowers the object slightly while still holding it in the center, presenting it to the group; everyone still faces the camera.
